</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>Under ideal injective binding, </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> = 1$</span><span>. Namespace laundering drives 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\gg</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> 1$</span><span>. The mutual information between agents and observations 
</span></span><span>degrades as:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">I(A;I) = H(I) - H(I|A) </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\leq</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\log</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">|</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{A}| - </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\log</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>When </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> exceeds a critical threshold </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_c$</span><span>, the system undergoes 
</span></span><span><span>an information-theoretic phase transition </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Cover2006</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>. Below this 
</span></span><span>threshold, modest effort can recover agent identity from behavioral patterns. 
</span><span>Above it, the combinatorial explosion of possible mappings makes attribution 
</span><span>computationally infeasible.
</span><span>
</span><span>This threshold is not universal but depends on the entropy rate of agent 
</span><span>behavior and the observational power of the platform. For typical social 
</span><span><span>platforms, empirical analysis suggests </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_c </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\approx</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> 3$</span><span>--</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$5$</span><span>: beyond this 
</span></span><span>point, most agents operate multiple persistent identities, and attribution 
</span><span>becomes unreliable.</span></code></pre></div></div>
