iv><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none; padding: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0px; overflow: auto; border-radius: 0.3em;"><code class="language-latex" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none;"><span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\section</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Formal Framework</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Definitions</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Namespace</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>A </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>namespace</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> is a triple </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{N}, </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{R}, </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\pi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">)$</span><span> where 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{N}$</span><span> is a set of names, </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{R}$</span><span> is a set of referents, and 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\pi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">: </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{N} </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\rightarrow</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\mathcal</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{R}$</span><span> is a mapping from names to referents.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Namespace Coherence</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>A namespace is </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>coherent</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> if </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\pi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> is injective: distinct names map to 
</span></span><span><span>distinct referents. It is </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>strongly coherent</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> if </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\pi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> is bijective and 
</span></span><span>persistent across time.
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Namespace Laundering</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Namespace laundering</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> occurs when a system permits the mapping </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\pi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> to 
</span></span><span>be violated or reset without cost, allowing referents to acquire new names or 
</span><span>names to be reassigned to new referents in ways that prevent historical 
</span><span>attribution.
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Attributional Entropy</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>Given observations </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$O$</span><span> and true agents </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$A$</span><span>, the </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>attributional entropy</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> 
</span></span><span>is:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">H_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{attr}} = H(A|O) = -</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\sum</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_{a,o} p(a,o) </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\log</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> p(a|o)
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>A system exhibits namespace laundering when </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$H_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{attr}} &gt; </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\epsilon</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> for 
</span></span><span><span>some tolerance threshold </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\epsilon</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> &gt; 0$</span><span>.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
