          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md active:scale-95 backdrop-blur-md Button_ghost__BUAoh" type="button" aria-label="Copiar al portapapeles" data-state="closed"><div class="relative"><div class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M12.5 3C13.3284 3 14 3.67157 14 4.5V6H15.5C16.3284 6 17 6.67157 17 7.5V15.5C17 16.3284 16.3284 17 15.5 17H7.5C6.67157 17 6 16.3284 6 15.5V14H4.5C3.67157 14 3 13.3284 3 12.5V4.5C3 3.67157 3.67157 3 4.5 3H12.5ZM14 12.5C14 13.3284 13.3284 14 12.5 14H7V15.5C7 15.7761 7.22386 16 7.5 16H15.5C15.7761 16 16 15.7761 16 15.5V7.5C16 7.22386 15.7761 7 15.5 7H14V12.5ZM4.5 4C4.22386 4 4 4.22386 4 4.5V12.5C4 12.7761 4.22386 13 4.5 13H12.5C12.7761 13 13 12.7761 13 12.5V4.5C13 4.22386 12.7761 4 12.5 4H4.5Z"></path></svg></div><div class="absolute top-0 left-0 transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="absolute top-0 left-0 transition-all opacity-0 scale-50" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M15.1883 5.10908C15.3699 4.96398 15.6346 4.96153 15.8202 5.11592C16.0056 5.27067 16.0504 5.53125 15.9403 5.73605L15.8836 5.82003L8.38354 14.8202C8.29361 14.9279 8.16242 14.9925 8.02221 14.9989C7.88203 15.0051 7.74545 14.9526 7.64622 14.8534L4.14617 11.3533L4.08172 11.2752C3.95384 11.0811 3.97542 10.817 4.14617 10.6463C4.31693 10.4755 4.58105 10.4539 4.77509 10.5818L4.85321 10.6463L7.96556 13.7586L15.1161 5.1794L15.1883 5.10908Z"></path></svg></div></div></button></div></div><div class="text-text-500 font-small p-3.5 pb-0">latex</div><div><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none; padding: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0px; overflow: auto; border-radius: 0.3em;"><code class="language-latex" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none;"><span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\section</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Regulatory Implications and Governance Models</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Current regulatory frameworks, including the EU's Digital Services Act and 
</span><span>proposed US platform regulations, treat identity verification as a policy 
</span><span><span>choice subject to privacy-harm balancing </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">DSA2022</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>. This framing is 
</span></span><span>inadequate. Namespace coherence is not a preference but a structural 
</span><span>requirement for any system claiming to mediate social or economic interaction.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Add citations to DSA, Section 230 debates, content moderation legal frameworks</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Three governance models merit consideration:
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\textbf</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Cryptographic self-sovereignty.</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> Users control their own cryptographic 
</span></span><span>identities, with platforms serving only as relay infrastructure...
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\textbf</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Federated attestation.</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> Trusted institutions provide verifiable 
</span></span><span>credentials that platforms can verify without centralizing identity control...
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\textbf</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Zero-knowledge reputation.</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> Systems can verify reputation thresholds 
</span></span><span>or behavioral history without learning identity, using cryptographic proofs...</span></code></pre></div></div>
