iv><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none; padding: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0px; overflow: auto; border-radius: 0.3em;"><code class="language-latex" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none;"><span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\section</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Economic Analysis of Identity Markets</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Namespace laundering can be understood as a market failure in which the price 
</span><span>of identity diverges from its social cost. In traditional markets, reputation 
</span><span>functions as a bond: sellers with valuable reputations have incentive to 
</span><span><span>maintain quality to preserve that asset </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Resnick2000</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>. 
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Digital platforms have destroyed this mechanism by making identity creation 
</span><span>cheaper than reputation maintenance...
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Expand with market microstructure analysis</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
