</span></span><span><span>expenditure </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Nakamoto2008,Bonneau2015</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>. While effective in limiting 
</span></span><span>identity proliferation, they externalize cost onto the environment and 
</span><span>privilege access to hardware and energy. Economic costs, such as staking or 
</span><span>fees, tie identity weight to capital, reinforcing existing inequalities 
