</span></span><span><span>There exists a critical identity dispersion </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_c$</span><span> such that for 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> &lt; </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_c$</span><span>, the system maintains approximate coherence, while for 
