<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Overview</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Your essay makes a powerful argument about Meta's knowing monetization of fraud. To make it more rigorous for academic publication, you need:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Extensive citation integration</strong> (currently only 1 source)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Formal theoretical framework</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Comparative analysis</strong> across platforms</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Legal/regulatory grounding</strong></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Empirical quantification</strong> where possible</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Counterargument engagement</strong></li>
</ol>
