iv><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none; padding: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0px; overflow: auto; border-radius: 0.3em;"><code class="language-latex" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none;"><span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\section</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Comparative Platform Analysis: Is Meta Unique?</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>While this essay focuses on Meta due to the availability of internal documents 
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">ReutersMeta2025</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>, evidence suggests that revenue-optimized enforcement 
</span></span><span>is endemic to advertiser-funded platforms rather than specific to Facebook.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Google and YouTube</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Google has faced parallel criticisms regarding fraudulent advertising on its 
</span><span><span>search and display networks </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Anderson2020Google</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>. In 2023, the company 
</span></span><span>reported blocking or removing 5.5 billion ads, yet acknowledged that enforcement 
</span><span><span>operates reactively rather than preventatively </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">GoogleAds2023</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>. Academic 
</span></span><span>analysis of Google's ad auction mechanisms demonstrates that penalty pricing 
</span><span><span>for suspected bad actors parallels Meta's approach </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Edelman2015</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Add citations:</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\bibitem</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Anderson2020Google</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>C. Anderson.
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span> Google's \</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$5 billion ad fraud problem.
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{The Markup}, January 15, 2020.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\bibitem</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{GoogleAds2023}
</span></span><span>Google Inc.
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> Ads safety report 2023.
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> Google Transparency Center, 2023.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\bibitem</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Edelman2015}
</span></span><span>B. Edelman and M. Schwarz.
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> Optimal auction design and equilibrium selection in sponsored search auctions.
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{American Economic Review}, 100(2):597--602, 2010.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{TikTok and Emerging Platforms}
</span></span><span>
</span><span>TikTok's rapid growth has coincided with reports of scam advertising targeting 
</span><span>younger users, particularly in financial services and cryptocurrency 
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Lorenz2022TikTok}. The platform's algorithmic recommendation system 
</span></span><span>amplifies engagement-maximizing content regardless of legitimacy, creating 
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">structural vulnerabilities parallel to those on Meta platforms </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Jiang2023}.
</span></span><span>
</span><span>[Add citations:]
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\bibitem</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Lorenz2022TikTok}
</span></span><span>T. Lorenz.
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> How TikTok became a scammer's paradise.
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{The Washington Post}, March 12, 2022.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\bibitem</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Jiang2023}
</span></span><span>J.~A. Jiang, E. Karahalios, and C. Fiesler.
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> Supporting serendipity: Opportunities and challenges for human-AI collaboration in qualitative analysis.
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\newblock</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Proceedings of the ACM on Human-Computer Interaction}, 7(CSCW1), 2023.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Structural Commonalities}
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Across platforms, three patterns emerge:
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{enumerate}
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\textbf</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Advertising revenue dominance:} Platforms deriving $</span><span>&gt;$80\</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(92, 99, 112); font-style: italic;">% of </span><span>
</span></span><span>revenue from advertising prioritize advertiser acquisition over advertiser 
</span><span><span>vetting </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Zuboff2019</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\textbf</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Reactive enforcement:</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> Moderation systems operate primarily in 
</span></span><span>response to external complaints (brand impersonation, regulatory pressure) 
</span><span><span>rather than proactive harm prevention </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Gillespie2018,Roberts2019</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\textbf</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>Penalty pricing over exclusion:</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> When fraudulent actors are 
</span></span><span>detected with moderate confidence, platforms increase costs rather than exclude, 
</span><span><span>preserving revenue while managing risk </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">Edelman2015</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">enumerate</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>This convergence suggests that the failures documented at Meta are not 
</span><span>idiosyncratic but emerge predictably from advertiser-funded business models 
</span><span>operating at scale.</span></code></pre></div></div>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
