iv><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none; padding: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0px; overflow: auto; border-radius: 0.3em;"><code class="language-latex" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none;"><span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\section</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Formal Framework: Monetized Foreseeability and Revenue-Calibrated Enforcement</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>To analyze Meta's conduct with precision, we formalize several key concepts.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Monetized Foreseeability</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>A platform exhibits </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>monetized foreseeability</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> with respect to harmful 
</span></span><span><span>activity </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$H$</span><span> if:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">enumerate</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> The platform maintains internal models estimating the frequency or volume 
</span></span><span><span>of </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$H$</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> Revenue </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R_H$</span><span> derived from </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$H$</span><span> is quantified in financial projections
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> Enforcement policies are calibrated such that </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R_H$</span><span> remains positive while 
</span></span><span><span>regulatory/reputational risk </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$C_R$</span><span> is bounded
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">enumerate</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>Formally: </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\exists</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^*$</span><span> such that enforcement operates at threshold </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^*$</span><span> 
</span></span><span><span>satisfying </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\arg</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\max</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> [R_H(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">) - C_R(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">)]$</span><span> where </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R_H(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^*)  &gt; 0$</span><span>.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Identity Churn Rate</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>Let </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$A$</span><span> denote the set of adversarial actors and </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$I_t$</span><span> the set of active 
</span></span><span><span>identities at time </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$t$</span><span>. The </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>identity churn rate</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> is:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\chi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> = </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\frac</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{|I_{t+</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\Delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> t} </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\setminus</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> I_t|}{|A| </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cdot</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\Delta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> t}
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>When </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\chi</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\gg</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> 1$</span><span>, actors routinely operate multiple disposable identities, 
</span></span><span>and enforcement removes instances rather than sources.
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Revenue-Calibrated Enforcement</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>Enforcement is </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>revenue-calibrated</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> if removal threshold </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> satisfies:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> = </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\arg</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\max</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">'} </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\left</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">[ R(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">') - </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\lambda</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cdot</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{rep}}(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">') </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\right</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">]
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>where </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">)$</span><span> is revenue under threshold </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span>, </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{rep}}(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">)$</span><span> 
</span></span><span><span>is reputational cost, and </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\lambda</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span> is the platform's sensitivity to reputation.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>Critically, this optimization occurs </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>given</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> rather than </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\emph</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span>against</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span> 
</span></span><span>the presence of harmful activity. The platform does not seek to minimize harm 
</span><span>directly but to optimize its economic exposure to harm's consequences.
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">definition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">proposition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Stabilization of Harm Under Revenue Optimization</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>If enforcement is revenue-calibrated and </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R_H(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^*) &gt; C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{fine}}$</span><span> where 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{fine}}$</span><span> represents expected regulatory penalties, then harmful activity 
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$H$</span><span> persists indefinitely at steady state determined by </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^*$</span><span>.
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">proposition</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">proof</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">[</span><span>Proof sketch</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">]</span><span>
</span></span><span>The platform's optimization problem is:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\max</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">_</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\quad</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> R_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{total}}(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">) - C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{rep}}(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">) - C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{fine}}
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>where </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{total}} = R_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{legit}} + R_H(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">)$</span><span> and </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{fine}}$</span><span> 
</span></span><span>is a sunk cost. The first-order condition is:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\frac</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\partial</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> R_H}{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\partial</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">} = </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\frac</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\partial</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{rep}}}{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\partial</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">}
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span>If </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$R_H(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^*) &gt; C_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{fine}}$</span><span>, the platform profits from harmful activity 
</span></span><span><span>net of penalties. Therefore, </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">^* &lt; 1$</span><span> (incomplete enforcement), and </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$H$</span><span> 
</span></span><span>persists at the level where marginal revenue from scams equals marginal 
</span><span><span>reputational cost. </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\qed</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">proof</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>This formalization demonstrates that Meta's documented behavior—setting fraud 
</span><span><span>detection thresholds at 95\</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(92, 99, 112); font-style: italic;">% \cite{ReutersMeta2025}—is not a technical </span><span>
</span></span><span>constraint but the solution to a revenue optimization problem under reputational 
</span><span>constraints.</span></code></pre></div></div>
