iv><pre class="code-block__code !my-0 !rounded-lg !text-sm !leading-relaxed" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none; padding: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0px; overflow: auto; border-radius: 0.3em;"><code class="language-latex" style="background: transparent; color: rgb(171, 178, 191); text-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 1px; font-family: var(--font-mono); direction: ltr; text-align: left; white-space: pre; word-spacing: normal; word-break: normal; line-height: 1.5; tab-size: 2; hyphens: none;"><span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\section</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Quantitative Analysis of Meta's Scam Revenue Model</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Revenue Estimates</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>According to Reuters </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">ReutersMeta2025</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>, Meta's internal documents estimate:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">itemize</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> 10\</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(92, 99, 112); font-style: italic;">% of advertising revenue derives from scams and prohibited goods</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> Meta's 2024 advertising revenue: approximately </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\$</span><span>131 billion
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> Implied scam-related revenue: </span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\$</span><span>13.1 billion annually
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">itemize</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>This figure vastly exceeds anticipated regulatory penalties. The EU's maximum 
</span><span><span>fine under the DSA is 6\</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(92, 99, 112); font-style: italic;">% of global revenue \cite{DSA2022}, or approximately </span><span>
</span></span><span><span>\</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$7.8 billion—still less than estimated scam revenue.
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Cost-Benefit Analysis of Enforcement}
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">Meta's penalty bid system </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cite</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{ReutersMeta2025} increases advertising costs for 
</span></span><span>suspected fraudsters. If we model this as:
</span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{itemize}
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> Base cost-per-impression: </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\$</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">C_0$</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> Penalty multiplier for suspected scams: </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\alpha</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\in</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> [1.5, 3.0]$</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\item</span><span> Fraud detection at threshold </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> = 0.95$</span><span>
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">itemize</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Then revenue under penalty pricing is:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">R_H(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">, </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\alpha</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">) = </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{Volume}(</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\theta</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">) </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cdot</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\alpha</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> </span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\cdot</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> C_0
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>Meta's internal analyses reportedly show that even with </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\alpha</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"> = 3$</span><span>, revenue 
</span></span><span><span>from scam ads operating below the 95\</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(92, 99, 112); font-style: italic;">% confidence threshold exceeds revenue lost </span><span>
</span></span><span>from removed ads. This demonstrates that penalty pricing is revenue-preserving 
</span><span>rather than harm-reducing.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\subsection</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token headline" style="color: rgb(209, 154, 102);">Identity Churn Dynamics</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>If fraudulent advertisers are removed at rate </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$r_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{remove}}$</span><span> and re-enter 
</span></span><span><span>at cost </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$c_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{entry}}$</span><span>, they persist so long as:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\begin</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\frac</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{R_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{scam}} - c_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{entry}}}{t_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{operation}}} &gt; 0
</span></span><span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);"></span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\end</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">{</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(198, 120, 221);">equation</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(171, 178, 191);">}</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>Where </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$t_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{operation}}$</span><span> is the average time before removal. Meta's 
</span></span><span><span>documented 96\</span><span class="token" style="color: rgb(92, 99, 112); font-style: italic;">% non-response rate to user reports \cite{ReutersMeta2025} </span><span>
</span></span><span><span>suggests </span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">$t_{</span><span class="token equation equation-command" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">\text</span><span class="token equation" style="color: rgb(152, 195, 121);">{operation}}$</span><span> is measured in weeks or months, far exceeding 
</span></span><span>the time required to profit from fraudulent campaigns.</span></code></pre></div></div>
